<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Wilderness" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Wilderness,</orth> 1) a tract of solitude and savageness, a desert: <bibl n="shak. luc 544" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 544</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.1.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 1, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 128</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.74" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.5.137" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 5, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.360" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 360</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 54</bibl>. 94 <emph>(a w. of sea).</emph><lb />2) wildness: <cit><quote>such a warped slip of w. ne'er issued from his blood,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.142" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 1, 142</bibl></cit> (<emph>slip of w.</emph> == wild slip).
